# Project Standards for __SERVICE_NAME__

## Directory Structure

Use numbered directories for easy sorting:
- `10_DOCS/` - Documentation, ADRs, guides
- `20_SRC/` - Source code
- `30_DATA/` - Data files (git-ignored)
- `40_RUNTIME/` - Runtime files, logs (git-ignored)
- `50_CONFIG/` - Configuration files
- `99_ARCHIVE/` - Deprecated code

## File Naming

- **No brackets**: Use dashes instead of `[]`, `()`, `{}`
- **Lowercase with dashes**: `my-service-name` not `MyServiceName`
- **Descriptive**: `user-authentication.ts` not `auth.ts`

## Code Standards

- **Health endpoints**: Always include `/health` that returns `{"ok": true}`
- **Tests required**: Every endpoint needs tests
- **TypeScript strict mode**: Enable all strict checks
- **No `any` types**: Use proper types everywhere
- **JSDoc comments**: Document complex functions

## Environment

- **Never commit `.env`**: Only commit `.env.example`
- **Use `50_CONFIG/`**: Store all config in numbered directory
- **Port from env**: Read `APP_PORT` from environment variable

## Docker

- **Health checks**: All services have Docker health checks
- **Multi-stage builds**: Use multi-stage Dockerfiles
- **Non-root user**: Run as node user in containers

## Git

- **Conventional commits**: `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `chore:`
- **Small commits**: One logical change per commit
- **Descriptive messages**: Explain the "why" not the "what"

## Code Quality

- **ESLint**: Fix all linting errors before committing
- **Prettier**: Auto-format on save
- **Husky hooks**: Run lint + tests pre-commit

## Documentation

- **ADRs**: Document all architectural decisions in `docs/decisions/`
- **README**: Keep README up-to-date with setup instructions
- **API docs**: Consider Swagger/OpenAPI for REST APIs
